A tremor measured at 3.7 occurred in Durban on Thursday. DURBAN - A tremor has shaken up Durban on Thursday at 13:19:24. The tremor measured at 3.7 on the Richter's scale according to the Council of Geoscience. It is thought to have lasted between three to four seconds. Social media users reported feeling it in Durban, Pietermaritzburg, Ballito, Port Shepstone and Hibberdene. There have been no reports of any damage.